WEBVTT

00:01.600 --> 00:02.669
Previously on Elementary:
Uh, we're here to
see Fiona Helbron,

00:02.700 --> 00:04.327
aka Mittens.

00:04.370 --> 00:05.792
FIONA:
They say autism is a spectrum,

00:05.830 --> 00:08.628
but it's really an array
of different conditions

00:08.670 --> 00:09.762
all lumped together.

00:09.810 --> 00:12.074
I prefer the term
"neuroatypical."

00:12.110 --> 00:15.409
The day Phil was arrested,
you walked me home, we talked.

00:15.440 --> 00:17.044
And I liked it.

00:17.810 --> 00:19.539
Can we do it again?

00:20.680 --> 00:22.181
I'm different, too.

00:22.220 --> 00:23.812
From other women you've dated.

00:23.850 --> 00:25.818
It takes a little
more work with me.

00:25.850 --> 00:27.750
I know that
because I've heard it

00:27.790 --> 00:29.724
from both my
previous boyfriends.

00:29.760 --> 00:31.125
I'm a little afraid.

00:31.160 --> 00:33.219
I'm a little afraid, too.

00:38.370 --> 00:40.691
*

00:40.740 --> 00:42.105
What?

00:42.140 --> 00:43.801
I was just marveling
at how you were able

00:43.840 --> 00:46.536
to sleep so soundly last night,
given the incessant sex noise.

00:46.580 --> 00:48.502
I didn't hear any sex noise.

00:48.540 --> 00:49.848
Through the wall
from next door.

00:49.880 --> 00:52.178
Trent and his new lover,

00:52.220 --> 00:53.812
putting the devil into hell
even as we speak.

00:53.850 --> 00:56.842
We just paid to have
his entire place soundproofed.

00:56.890 --> 00:58.414
Not well enough, apparently.

00:58.450 --> 01:00.156
Oh, you're crazy.

01:00.190 --> 01:01.657
Am I?

01:01.690 --> 01:03.624
So, Trent has a new girlfriend.

01:03.660 --> 01:05.753
You have a new girlfriend.
Why is this a problem?

01:05.790 --> 01:07.121
'Cause it's their fourth night

01:07.160 --> 01:08.457
of marathon activity
in the last week.

01:08.500 --> 01:09.797
It's distracting.

01:09.830 --> 01:11.366
Quiet is indispensable
to my process.

01:11.400 --> 01:12.469
How do you not hear it?

01:12.500 --> 01:14.138
Just luclq I guess.

01:14.170 --> 01:15.660
Perhaps it entered
your mind unconsciously.

01:15.700 --> 01:18.339
Were your dreams filled with two
flounders slapping together?

01:18.370 --> 01:21.168
A ketchup bottle being
squeezed repeatedly

01:21.210 --> 01:23.269
whilst a nearby walrus
issues a death rattle?

01:23.310 --> 01:24.379
Okay, I get it.

01:24.410 --> 01:26.378
I assure you, you do not.

01:33.260 --> 01:34.784
Don't.
Don't what?

01:34.820 --> 01:37.653
Mess with him.
I'm serious.

01:37.690 --> 01:39.351
No chain saw art in the study,

01:39.400 --> 01:41.356
no marching bands
in the library.

01:41.400 --> 01:44.198
He's a nice guy, and we've just
convinced him to move back in.

01:44.230 --> 01:46.232
Not promising anything.

01:46.270 --> 01:48.192
If uprooting Trent
is the price of justice,

01:48.240 --> 01:49.639
history will be
on our side.

01:49.670 --> 01:51.206
Finish your coffee
and get dressed.

01:51.240 --> 01:52.229
While you slumbered

01:52.280 --> 01:53.474
we received a call.

01:53.510 --> 01:55.205
_ Potential client
IS on hIS way here.

01:56.780 --> 01:59.248
(door closing)

02:01.180 --> 02:04.741
HOLMES:
Must confess,
Mr. Springer, your call

02:04.790 --> 02:06.382
took us by surprise.

02:06.420 --> 02:08.479
We wouldn't have expected you
to request our services.

02:08.520 --> 02:11.819
Why? Because you put two of my
partners behind bars last month?

02:11.860 --> 02:15.626
Not the sort of thing
that tends to win us fans.

02:15.660 --> 02:17.594
It worked out in my favor.

02:17.630 --> 02:19.166
So they didn't commit a murder,

02:19.200 --> 02:20.929
so much as provide you
a murder-tunity.

02:20.970 --> 02:22.733
Are you okay?

02:22.770 --> 02:24.806
He'll be fine.

02:24.840 --> 02:28.276
This is my son Brian.
He's the reason I called.

02:28.310 --> 02:31.347
And you're right,
I don't like you.

02:31.380 --> 02:32.608
But you're the best.

02:32.650 --> 02:34.515
And this has nothing
to do with my firm.

02:36.490 --> 02:37.946
Missing Persons case.

02:37.990 --> 02:40.208
A doctor named
Vincent Bader.

02:40.260 --> 02:41.909
No one's seen him
for srx days.

02:41.960 --> 02:43.825
That's everything the cops have.

02:43.860 --> 02:44.952
And you came
in possession

02:44.990 --> 02:46.628
of a police file how?

02:46.660 --> 02:48.491
Let's just say
the firm's security team

02:48.530 --> 02:50.691
has its share
of retired detectives.

02:50.730 --> 02:52.288
Oh.

02:52.340 --> 02:54.467
Pain management specialist,
he co-owns

02:54.500 --> 02:56.206
a center near Lenox Hill.

02:56.240 --> 02:57.468
And what's your interest in him?

02:57.510 --> 02:59.205
Minimal.

02:59.240 --> 03:01.299
Brian's a patient,
you'll see that in the file.

03:03.280 --> 03:04.542
So you're a person of interest

03:04.580 --> 03:05.604
in the doctor's
disappearance.

03:05.650 --> 03:07.311
There was
an altercation

03:07.350 --> 03:08.874
outside his office

03:08.920 --> 03:11.411
two days before he went missing
and threats were overheard?

03:11.450 --> 03:13.281
Tell them.

03:14.990 --> 03:16.753
I never did
anything to him.

03:16.790 --> 03:18.451
I was just mad.

03:18.490 --> 03:19.923
SPRINGER:
The kid's never even
hit a baseball,

03:19.960 --> 03:21.552
let alone a man.

03:21.600 --> 03:22.794
So you're going through

03:22.830 --> 03:25.594
prescription opioid
withdrawal, hmm?

03:25.630 --> 03:28.929
You were seeing a pain
specialist and now you're not.

03:28.970 --> 03:30.608
Brian's always been frail.

03:30.640 --> 03:34.531
One injury or another his
whole life, mostly back pain.

03:34.580 --> 03:36.445
WATSON:
This argument
people overheard,

03:36.480 --> 03:38.368
Dr. Bader cut you off your meds?

03:38.410 --> 03:40.810
No, I did. Bader's
the one that got him hooked.

03:40.850 --> 03:42.909
Brian was trying to get
some pills from him,

03:42.950 --> 03:46.386
despite my instructions
to the contrary.

03:46.420 --> 03:48.456
Let's get you some tea.

03:48.490 --> 03:50.526
(quietly):
Go ahead.

04:00.740 --> 04:02.332
What?

04:02.370 --> 04:04.304
Just going through my theories

04:04.340 --> 04:07.309
to the origins of your son's
chronic pain.

04:07.340 --> 04:09.342
Not that I'll ever
be able to prove it.

04:09.380 --> 04:11.348
I remember there were
a few photographs of him

04:11.380 --> 04:12.415
in your office.

04:12.450 --> 04:13.917
He was very partial to wearing

04:13.950 --> 04:16.589
long sleeves,
long trousers in warm weather.

04:16.620 --> 04:18.349
At first I didn't
think anything of it,

04:18.390 --> 04:20.551
but now I'm wondering
whether it was to hide bruises.

04:22.690 --> 04:23.918
Yes.

04:23.960 --> 04:26.895
Whatever chronic
back injury he has,

04:26.930 --> 04:29.569
it began at your hand,
did it not?

04:29.600 --> 04:31.591
There are two things
you should know,

04:31.630 --> 04:33.029
Mr. Springer.

04:33.070 --> 04:35.459
First is that I'm going
to punch you in the face.

04:36.570 --> 04:37.901
(groans)

04:37.940 --> 04:40.738
Second... is that we'll
take your case.

04:43.410 --> 04:45.401
*

05:18.550 --> 05:21.610
Vince called me from his office
Thursday afternoon.

05:21.650 --> 05:23.948
Said he was going to the gym
after work-- he has

05:23.990 --> 05:25.617
a membership
in the city.

05:25.650 --> 05:27.789
And then he had
a continuing ed dinner

05:27.820 --> 05:31.051
at a restaurant in midtown.

05:31.090 --> 05:33.797
He never made it to either.

05:33.830 --> 05:35.957
_There are two cars in the_
driveway-- IS one of them hIS?

05:36.000 --> 05:37.092
He takes the train.

05:37.130 --> 05:38.620
You said
you were hired

05:38.670 --> 05:40.137
by the father of the kid

05:40.170 --> 05:41.762
who was questioned by the cops?

05:41.800 --> 05:43.768
My inquiries are
on the young man's behalf.

05:43.810 --> 05:46.062
Is that all right?

05:46.110 --> 05:49.034
It's not like he did anything.

05:49.080 --> 05:50.399
You may be right.

05:50.450 --> 05:53.374
In my experience,
the guilty party

05:53.420 --> 05:56.071
rarely hires someone
to investigate.

05:56.120 --> 05:57.883
But, if you don't
mind me asking you,

05:57.920 --> 06:00.115
why do you think he's innocent?

06:00.160 --> 06:02.082
For a woman who's_
husband has been missmg

06:02.120 --> 06:04.122
for almost a week,
you seem rather unconcerned.

06:04.160 --> 06:07.527
That's because
I'm not concerned-- I'm angry.

06:07.560 --> 06:09.118
Vince isn't lying

06:09.160 --> 06:12.493
in a ditch somewhere,
he ran off with some redhead.

06:12.540 --> 06:14.792
Probably a patient or a nurse.

06:14.840 --> 06:16.034
Someone he met at work.

06:16.070 --> 06:17.708
And you think this because?

06:17.740 --> 06:18.729
My two girlfriends

06:18.770 --> 06:20.078
saw him buying her lunch

06:20.110 --> 06:21.202
in the city a few weeks ago.

06:21.240 --> 06:22.446
You know, looking over his
shoulder, the whole deal.

06:22.480 --> 06:26.519
They said she was so skinny they
wanted to send over a steak.

06:26.550 --> 06:28.438
I asked Vince

06:28.480 --> 06:30.710
about it-- he wouldn't
tell me who she was.

06:30.750 --> 06:32.411
So what else
am I supposed to think?

06:32.460 --> 06:34.451
You mentioned none of this

06:34.490 --> 06:36.629
when you reported him missing
to the police.

06:36.660 --> 06:39.458
IfI had, they wouldn't have
looked for him at all.

06:39.500 --> 06:42.094
My cousin's a cop.
I know how it works.

06:42.130 --> 06:44.462
You should still prepare
yourself for the worst.

06:44.500 --> 06:46.934
The details of your
husband's disappearance,

06:46.970 --> 06:48.961
and the abandonment
of his business,

06:49.000 --> 06:54.108
they don't absolutely fit the
profile of a cheating husband.

06:56.750 --> 06:59.776
There's another reason
I think that Vince is fine.

07:01.080 --> 07:03.048
Let me show you.

07:18.230 --> 07:20.164
Hmm...

07:20.200 --> 07:22.168
So, this is meant to indicate
that your husband

07:22.200 --> 07:24.134
didn't fall into harm's way
because it looks like

07:24.170 --> 07:25.728
he's planning a small invasion.

07:25.770 --> 07:27.169
Vince is a prepper.

07:27.210 --> 07:28.802
Are you familiar with the term?

07:28.840 --> 07:30.705
Yes, he's convinced
that society as we know it

07:30.750 --> 07:33.639
is on the verge of collapse
and it's his duty to be ready.

07:33.680 --> 07:35.170
I didn't care
one way or the other,

07:35.220 --> 07:36.642
as long as he didn't
blow too much money.

07:36.690 --> 07:37.748
Made him feel better.

07:37.790 --> 07:38.745
Point is, Vince is

07:38.790 --> 07:40.815
obsessed with
self-defense.

07:40.860 --> 07:42.748
He's not someone
a mugger or a kidnapper

07:42.790 --> 07:44.087
is going to get
a jump on.

07:44.130 --> 07:45.586
Don't get me wrong, though.

07:45.630 --> 07:47.894
When he turns up,
I'm going to kill him.

07:47.930 --> 07:50.262
MAN:
I don't buy it.

07:50.300 --> 07:52.188
Vince would never
cheat on Jennifer.

07:52.230 --> 07:53.868
He loves her.

07:53.900 --> 07:56.903
So the alternative is that
something happened to him.

07:56.940 --> 07:59.500
Well, that's what
I'm worried about.

07:59.540 --> 08:01.235
But, hey, I'll be
thrilled if I'm wrong.

08:01.280 --> 08:02.679
Please.

08:02.710 --> 08:04.507
So you said you were
out of the ofﬁce

08:04.550 --> 08:06.643
the day he disappeared?

08:06.680 --> 08:08.841
My girlfriend had a...
family thing

08:08.880 --> 08:10.518
on Lake Ronkonkoma.

08:10.550 --> 08:12.245
I took a long
weekend.

08:12.290 --> 08:14.656
Vince and I talked on the phone
that day-- work stuff.

08:14.690 --> 08:17.124
He seemed normal.

08:17.160 --> 08:19.549
Julie Monahan, drug rep.

08:19.600 --> 08:20.919
What about her?
Mrs. Bader mentioned

08:20.960 --> 08:23.064
something about
a redhead to my partner.

08:24.730 --> 08:26.937
Julie makes her rounds here
every month or so.

08:26.970 --> 08:28.597
She's flirty.

08:28.640 --> 08:29.959
With all the guys.

08:30.010 --> 08:32.228
Female docs, too, if it works.

08:32.270 --> 08:34.306
It's her job to be that way,
it isn't real.

08:34.340 --> 08:38.049
I never thought Vince would
have... acted on it.

08:38.080 --> 08:39.945
Do you mind
ifI hang on to this?

08:39.980 --> 08:40.844
Sure.

08:42.850 --> 08:44.317
BELL:
You know, you didn't need

08:44.350 --> 08:46.045
to bring an attorney,
Ms. Monahan.

08:46.090 --> 08:47.819
Far as we know, you're
not in any trouble.

08:47.860 --> 08:49.589
If Vincent Bader's all right,

08:49.630 --> 08:51.279
no crime has
been committed.

08:51.330 --> 08:53.548
I'm going to cut you off,
Detective. You misunderstand.

08:53.600 --> 08:55.693
Ms. Monahan didn't know
Dr. Bader was missing

08:55.730 --> 08:56.958
until you called her.

08:57.000 --> 08:58.592
Now that you did,

08:58.630 --> 08:59.995
she may have information
that could help.

09:00.040 --> 09:01.860
Whatever it is,
she's worried that

09:01.900 --> 09:04.266
it might get her in trouble,
that's why she brought you.

09:04.310 --> 09:05.607
Yes.

09:05.640 --> 09:07.107
Is whatever she did

09:07.140 --> 09:08.698
less bad than what she thinks
happened to Dr. Bader?

09:08.740 --> 09:10.571
By about
a thousand miles.

09:10.610 --> 09:12.305
All right,
I can't make any promises,

09:12.350 --> 09:14.568
but if that's true, I'm sure
Ms. Monahan's cooperation

09:14.620 --> 09:16.212
will be taken into account,

09:16.250 --> 09:18.309
and I'd throw whatever support
I could that way.

09:20.660 --> 09:24.255
A few weeks ago,
Vince came to me with a problem.

09:24.290 --> 09:26.258
He had been selling narcotics

09:26.290 --> 09:28.724
out of his practice
to drug dealers.

09:28.760 --> 09:30.091
Oxycodone,

09:30.130 --> 09:32.121
hydrocodone, morphine.

09:32.170 --> 09:34.661
He tell you the dealers' names?

09:36.300 --> 09:38.268
He told me
it started out small--

09:38.310 --> 09:41.074
he just needed to make some
extra money on the side--

09:41.110 --> 09:43.772
but then they kept wanting more

09:43.810 --> 09:47.143
and they threatened
to hurt him if he stopped.

09:47.180 --> 09:49.944
This had been
going on for months.

09:49.990 --> 09:51.309
Then he got a notification

09:51.350 --> 09:53.284
from the Bureau
of Narcotics Enforcement

09:53.320 --> 09:56.084
saying that his practice
was up for an audit.

09:56.120 --> 09:57.656
An audit?
They come
to your offices

09:57.690 --> 10:00.352
and inspect all of your
controlled substances.

10:00.400 --> 10:01.958
They check your dispensing
records,

10:02.000 --> 10:03.865
literally count
every pill.

10:03.900 --> 10:05.322
If Bader was
selling pills illegally,

10:05.370 --> 10:06.837
the count would be short.

10:06.870 --> 10:09.088
The state would launch
a full investigation.

10:09.140 --> 10:11.165
How short are we talking?

10:11.210 --> 10:14.031
Over $200,000 in pills.

10:14.080 --> 10:16.378
Vince panicked.

10:16.410 --> 10:20.312
He asked for my help and I...

10:20.350 --> 10:25.117
lent him enough inventory,
off the books,

10:25.150 --> 10:27.380
so that when
the BNE came

10:27.420 --> 10:28.785
came to do their count,

10:28.820 --> 10:30.185
everything appeared
to be in order.

10:30.230 --> 10:32.186
After that, he gave

10:32.230 --> 10:33.697
the pills back to me.

10:33.730 --> 10:35.322
He'd bought himself
the time he needed.

10:35.360 --> 10:37.294
It would be years
before another audit,

10:37.330 --> 10:39.798
_ so he could _
pad his records over time

10:39.840 --> 10:41.728
to make everything even out.

10:41.770 --> 10:43.431
Why exactly did you help him?

10:43.470 --> 10:47.702
Because it put him in her pocket
instead of the drug dealers.

10:47.740 --> 10:50.709
She earned herself
a big customer for life.

10:50.750 --> 10:53.913
After that, he swore to me

10:53.950 --> 10:56.316
that he would
break it off with the dealers.

10:56.350 --> 10:58.147
Whatever it took.

10:58.190 --> 11:02.251
If Vince is missing, I have to
think those guys are involved.

11:03.760 --> 11:05.125
Watson?

11:05.160 --> 11:06.718
Hey, where are you?

11:06.760 --> 11:09.297
Midtown. I stopped
by Vincent Bader's gym.

11:09.330 --> 11:11.321
His wife said he had
his gym bag with him

11:11.370 --> 11:12.769
the morning he disappeared.

11:12.800 --> 11:14.336
It hasn't turned up.

11:14.370 --> 11:16.736
I just verified for myself
that he never made it here.

11:16.770 --> 11:18.169
It's possible he met
with foul play

11:18.210 --> 11:19.359
between his office and here.

11:19.410 --> 11:22.436
It's also possible that he never
intended to go to the gym.

11:22.480 --> 11:24.243
The bag might have contained
extra clothes.

11:24.280 --> 11:26.407
He might not fit the profile
of a cheating husband,

11:26.450 --> 11:28.179
but he might be
a runaway husband.

11:28.220 --> 11:30.085
Especially if he recently
broke off business

11:30.120 --> 11:31.189
with drug traffickers.

11:31.220 --> 11:32.414
So you got my message.

11:32.450 --> 11:33.917
If they intended him harm,

11:33.960 --> 11:35.450
he might be on the lam.

11:35.490 --> 11:37.128
Any progress identifying them?

11:37.160 --> 11:38.855
Marcus just passed Bader's
phone records on to Narcotics.

11:38.890 --> 11:41.495
Missing Persons
already went through them,

11:41.530 --> 11:43.395
but now that we know
what we're looking for,

11:43.430 --> 11:45.398
maybe something will leap out.

11:45.430 --> 11:46.397
(doorbell buzzes)

11:46.430 --> 11:47.966
Oh, someone's at the door.

11:48.000 --> 11:49.399
Uh, I'll see you later.

11:54.480 --> 11:56.038
Fiona, hi.

11:56.080 --> 11:57.399
Uh, come on in.

11:57.450 --> 12:00.010
Is Sherlock home?

12:00.050 --> 12:01.347
No, he's out right now,

12:01.380 --> 12:03.086
but he should be back
in a little bit,

12:03.120 --> 12:04.781
if you want to wait.

12:04.820 --> 12:06.412
Do you know how soon
he'll be here?

12:06.450 --> 12:08.111
Uh, maybe 45 minutes.

12:08.160 --> 12:09.787
I'll come back another time.

12:09.830 --> 12:13.425
I prepared what I want
to say to Sherlock.

12:13.460 --> 12:14.427
I timed it,

12:14.460 --> 12:16.189
so I know how long
it'll take.

12:16.230 --> 12:17.891
And if I don't know
how long it'll take,

12:17.930 --> 12:20.091
I won't know
when I'll get back to my office

12:20.140 --> 12:22.062
or what time
I'll finish my work,

12:22.100 --> 12:24.466
and I won't like that.

12:25.910 --> 12:27.730
(door closes)

12:29.810 --> 12:31.778
(clattering)
Hey.

12:31.810 --> 12:32.970
When did you get back?

12:33.020 --> 12:34.442
Just arrived.

12:34.480 --> 12:36.812
I saw the information
Marcus sent over.

12:36.850 --> 12:39.489
Emmett Wahl.

12:39.520 --> 12:42.785
The fruit of
the narcotic squad's labor?
Yeah. They recognized

12:42.830 --> 12:44.980
a number on _Bader's
phone records right away.

12:45.030 --> 12:46.281
But it wasn't Wahl's--
it was his mother's.

12:46.330 --> 12:47.797
They have a wiretap on it.

12:47.830 --> 12:48.922
Apparently he's been
doing business

12:48.960 --> 12:50.461
out of her place
for a while now.

12:50.500 --> 12:53.389
He acquires product
for a pill trafficking group

12:53.440 --> 12:55.089
called the Silver Rail.

12:55.140 --> 12:56.801
Named after the passenger train

12:56.840 --> 12:57.966
that runs up and down
the East Coast.

12:58.010 --> 12:59.409
A reference to their territory?

12:59.440 --> 13:01.237
I would say you could
ask Wahl yourself

13:01.280 --> 13:03.009
when we talk to him,
but I wouldn't bother.

