You said

27:42.890 --> 27:44.118
you're a doctor--
do you know about

27:44.160 --> 27:45.718
impingement syndrome?

27:45.760 --> 27:48.251
Inflammation of the tendons
in the rotator cuff

27:48.300 --> 27:50.325
caused by repeated
stress. Why?

27:50.360 --> 27:54.069
I messed up my shoulders
swimming in high school.

27:54.100 --> 27:56.739
I couldn't have swung a hatchet
ifI wanted to.

27:59.510 --> 28:01.899
I was never in...

28:01.940 --> 28:04.272
the Marines, okay?

28:04.310 --> 28:07.279
They turned me down
because of my shoulders

28:07.310 --> 28:09.039
when I tried to sign up.

28:09.080 --> 28:12.311
You got to be able
to check that. Right?

28:16.120 --> 28:17.212
(sighs)

28:18.990 --> 28:21.129
All right, so let's say
he's telling the truth.

28:21.160 --> 28:23.424
Bader and someone else drive
out to the bunker together,

28:23.460 --> 28:25.360
they discover the
whole thing is fake,

28:25.400 --> 28:27.391
so the other guy
flies off the handle.

28:27.430 --> 28:30.194
Maybe it was someone Bader
convinced to buy into The Keep,

28:30.240 --> 28:32.458
so he blamed Bader for
him losing his money.

28:32.510 --> 28:34.137
Maybe, but we still
don't know what they

28:34.180 --> 28:35.909
were doing out there
in the first place.

28:35.940 --> 28:37.908
Check Wright's Marine story.

28:37.950 --> 28:40.145
Make sure this
shoulder thing is real.

28:40.180 --> 28:42.774
If it is, we got to
start combing through
his other clients.

28:42.820 --> 28:46.312
At the minimum, he's looking at
fraud and hindering prosecution.

28:46.350 --> 28:49.285
I'm pretty sure he'll give up
that list of names now.

28:49.320 --> 28:51.424
HOLMES:
Apologies I don't have

28:51.460 --> 28:54.190
any wine to offer you.
Today's a weekday.

28:54.230 --> 28:56.949
Tomorrow's also a weekday.

28:57.000 --> 28:59.195
I don't drink wine on weekdays.

28:59.230 --> 29:02.290
It affects my sleep.
I've tested it.

29:02.340 --> 29:04.103
Ah. Much as I would have.

29:04.140 --> 29:06.199
The water is fine.

29:13.510 --> 29:16.274
Thank you. (pants)

29:16.320 --> 29:20.188
Uh, Watson said you stopped by.
1-1 texted you...

29:20.220 --> 29:22.256
I have something
to say.

29:23.520 --> 29:26.057
I memorized it ahead of time...

29:26.090 --> 29:28.297
because it's hard.

29:28.330 --> 29:30.389
Well, I shall endeavor
not to interrupt.

29:31.970 --> 29:34.336
You're very considerate of me.

29:34.370 --> 29:37.294
I've noticed that.
Very careful.

29:37.340 --> 29:40.229
It's one of the things
I liked most about you

29:40.270 --> 29:42.579
at first.

29:42.610 --> 29:45.408
When we first started dating,
it felt like you liked me

29:45.450 --> 29:48.374
because I was a woman
that you liked.

29:48.420 --> 29:51.810
It didn't matter that
I was neuroatypical.

29:51.850 --> 29:53.317
That is...

29:53.350 --> 29:55.818
it mattered, obviously.

29:55.860 --> 29:59.887
But.. it also...
didn't matter to you.

29:59.930 --> 30:03.229
And now it feels like you're
not being yourself with me.

30:03.260 --> 30:05.069
You're being careful.
You're doing

30:05.100 --> 30:07.159
what you think you're
supposed to do,

30:07.200 --> 30:09.134
because I'm different.

30:09.170 --> 30:13.004
And... that makes me feel
like a project

30:13.040 --> 30:16.077
or a problem for you to solve.

30:16.110 --> 30:17.270
And...

30:17.310 --> 30:19.904
that isn't the way
I want to feel.

30:19.950 --> 30:21.918
So...

30:21.950 --> 30:23.918
Iam...

30:23.950 --> 30:26.180
breaking up with you.

30:28.360 --> 30:30.988
Thank you for the water.

30:35.360 --> 30:38.568
Marcus and I were going through
the names of Keep members,

30:38.600 --> 30:41.296
when this one caught our eye.
Clyde Staller.

30:41.340 --> 30:44.036
BELL:
There's not much about him
online except that he made

30:44.070 --> 30:46.334
a truckload of money
about three years ago

30:46.370 --> 30:47.564
selling a sobeare startup

30:47.610 --> 30:50.101
and that he really hates
paying taxes.

30:50.140 --> 30:52.404
Sounds just like anyone else
who'd be on this list.

30:52.450 --> 30:55.044
What made him jump out?
I recognized

30:55.080 --> 30:56.638
the name of his company,
Ardent Army.

30:56.680 --> 30:58.216
Earlier today, Sherlock and I

30:58.250 --> 31:00.047
were looking
at discussion boards

31:00.090 --> 31:01.182
that Bader chatted on.

31:01.220 --> 31:02.881
One of the preppers
he talked to

31:02.920 --> 31:04.387
had the username ArdentArmy.
Bader recommended

31:04.430 --> 31:06.386
The Keep to Staller
on that board.

31:06.430 --> 31:09.092
And from the looks of the date
in Wright's file,

31:09.130 --> 31:11.519
Staller bought in based on that.
So, if anyone

31:11.570 --> 31:14.061
would be mad at Bader
over the bunkers being fake,

31:14.100 --> 31:16.295
you figure
it's got to be this guy.

31:16.340 --> 31:17.932
BELL:
Staller loved
to rant about

31:17.970 --> 31:19.369
how much he mistrusts
the government.

31:19.410 --> 31:22.004
Maybe we can lure him
to do it in person.

31:29.020 --> 31:31.409
Staller's inside.
Got here just after I did.

31:31.450 --> 31:34.214
His skinny jeans make the
odds of a concealed firearm

31:34.260 --> 31:35.955
quite slim.
That's good to know.

31:35.990 --> 31:37.287
How'd it go
with Fiona?

31:37.320 --> 31:39.322
We'll discuss it later.

31:41.560 --> 31:43.152
Whoa, you guys have
the wrong idea.

31:43.200 --> 31:45.088
I don't know anything
about a murder.

31:45.130 --> 31:48.429
You'd be surprised how
many confessions start that way.

31:48.470 --> 31:51.507
All right, you think I was mad
because The Keep was a fraud.

31:51.540 --> 31:54.532
I knew The Keep was a fraud.

31:54.580 --> 31:57.140
It's why I was interested
in it in the first place.

31:57.180 --> 31:58.374
Do explain.

31:58.410 --> 32:00.139
I'd like to get my wallet out,

32:00.180 --> 32:02.239
show you my driver's license.
Is that okay?

32:02.280 --> 32:03.542
Why don't I get it for you.

32:03.580 --> 32:05.116
Yeah.

32:09.220 --> 32:10.983
My real name is Jeff Danks.

32:11.030 --> 32:12.622
I'm an editor
for Bunksaw.com.

32:12.660 --> 32:15.390
_You're_
a journalist.
Yes. I'm...

32:15.430 --> 32:19.059
writing an expos
on The Keep.

32:21.140 --> 32:23.495
"'Ayn Rand Shrugged'

32:23.540 --> 32:25.531
"by Jeff Danks.
Of course a doomsday bunker

32:25.570 --> 32:26.559
"for the rich is a scam.

32:26.610 --> 32:27.668
"Aren't these the guys
who insist,

32:27.710 --> 32:29.405
'Every man for himself'?"

32:29.440 --> 32:31.408
Clyde Staller,
tech entrepreneur,

32:31.450 --> 32:33.668
is a persona
you created online.

32:33.710 --> 32:35.678
Newly-minted millionaire,
no formal education.

32:35.720 --> 32:38.518
The lack of history is a
virtue rather than a red flag.

32:38.550 --> 32:40.518
Spout a few
of the right political views,

32:40.550 --> 32:42.381
you can infiltrate
the prepper boards.

32:42.420 --> 32:44.422
So how did you know?

32:45.760 --> 32:47.557
I started out doing a piece
on preppers.

32:47.590 --> 32:50.229
Heard about The Keep
and started digging.

32:50.260 --> 32:53.525
So many people fall
for cons like this

32:53.570 --> 32:55.367
because the top secret thing
convinces them

32:55.400 --> 32:57.664
not to look closely.
They're not supposed to know

32:57.700 --> 32:59.509
who Wright's
military advisor is,

32:59.540 --> 33:01.679
so they accept that they can't.

33:01.710 --> 33:04.144
But it leaves a paper trail
when you try to buy

33:04.180 --> 33:06.205
30,000 gallons of diesel.

33:06.250 --> 33:08.673
It wasn't hard to confirm
that they never did.

33:08.720 --> 33:11.188
Same goes for his stockpile
of food, the antibiotics,

33:11.220 --> 33:12.744
his generator.

33:12.790 --> 33:14.553
Thank you very
much, Mr. Danks.

33:14.590 --> 33:16.683
You've been very
helpful. We need to go

33:16.720 --> 33:18.449
to Vincent Bader's house.
Specifically,

33:18.490 --> 33:20.026
his garage.

33:20.060 --> 33:22.494
(whirring)

33:29.540 --> 33:32.509
BELL:
Imagine how much help
we could be

33:32.540 --> 33:34.201
if you told us
what we're looking for.

33:34.240 --> 33:36.037
Well, I'm not looking
for anything.

33:36.080 --> 33:38.674
I'm hoping to confirm
an item's absence.

33:38.710 --> 33:41.076
Okay, so what
are we not looking for?

33:41.120 --> 33:44.248
As Mr. Danks ticked off
the bunker's non-inventory,

33:44.290 --> 33:46.508
a new theory started to develop.

33:46.550 --> 33:48.711
This is a bug-out bag.

33:48.760 --> 33:52.321
It's the absolute essentials
that a doomsday prepper

33:52.360 --> 33:53.725
would grab
when Armageddon

33:53.760 --> 33:56.354
finally dawns.
This particular bag

33:56.400 --> 33:58.527
is sold as a kit.

34:00.500 --> 34:03.389
Included in that kit...

34:03.440 --> 34:07.399
Is a multipurpose tool,
like the one the killer used.

34:07.440 --> 34:10.079
Said tool is not in this bag.

34:10.110 --> 34:12.078
We've been thinking
the tool belonged

34:12.110 --> 34:14.146
to a different prepper.
Bader's killer.

34:14.180 --> 34:16.478
Or, prior to the discovery
that the bunker was bare,

34:16.520 --> 34:19.409
that it was a weapon of
opportunity found at the scene.

34:19.450 --> 34:20.781
But Bader brought the tool
himself.

34:20.820 --> 34:22.788
It must've been
in his gym bag.

34:22.820 --> 34:25.186
But why? We still don't know
what he was doing there.

34:25.230 --> 34:28.449
That's where the new theory,
courtesy of Mr. Danks, comes in.

34:28.500 --> 34:30.650
I know why Bader went
to the bunker that night.

34:30.700 --> 34:32.190
And with whom.

34:37.540 --> 34:39.167
Appreciate you coming down,
Dr. Wallace.

34:39.210 --> 34:40.768
Hope you didn't have to juggle
too many patients.

34:40.810 --> 34:43.335
Not a problem. Anything
I can do to help.

34:43.380 --> 34:46.201
Great. You know Ms. Watson.
This is Detective Bell

34:46.250 --> 34:48.775
and Sherlock Holmes.
Have a seat.

34:48.820 --> 34:50.776
(grunts)

34:50.820 --> 34:55.359
Some information's come to light
about Dr. Bader's murder.

34:55.390 --> 34:57.688
It could have an impact
on your practice,

34:57.720 --> 35:00.188
so... we thought
you ought to know.

35:00.230 --> 35:03.154
His wife told me
that he was killed in a...

35:03.200 --> 35:04.861
doomsday bunker.

35:04.900 --> 35:06.697
That another prepper killed him.

35:06.730 --> 35:07.890
HOLMES:
We believe that
that's what the killer

35:07.930 --> 35:10.160
intended us to think.
Your partner

35:10.200 --> 35:12.737
had gotten himself involved
with a group of pill traffickers

35:12.770 --> 35:15.136
called the Silver Rail.
We have reason to think

35:15.180 --> 35:17.808
he tried to break things off
with them but couldn't.

35:17.840 --> 35:21.241
You think Vince was killed
by drug dealers?
We would

35:21.280 --> 35:24.317
have thought that, except
they didn't know he was dead.
There was

35:24.350 --> 35:26.784
someone else who had reason to
kill him over his bad deCI5ions.

35:26.820 --> 35:29.254
You. Because of the mess
he'd gotten into

35:29.290 --> 35:30.882
could have brought
your whole practice down.

35:30.920 --> 35:32.888
HOLMES:
We'd been asking ourselves
for some time

35:32.930 --> 35:35.296
what Dr. Bader was doing
in the bunker that night.

35:35.330 --> 35:36.888
He had a need.

35:36.930 --> 35:39.160
He had a drug gang
breathing down his neck.

35:39.200 --> 35:41.168
He had weathered _
one government inspection,

35:41.200 --> 35:43.339
but his luck couldn't hold out.
He needed pain pills,

35:43.370 --> 35:45.167
and he needed lots of them.

35:45.210 --> 35:48.805
The infirmary at The Keep should
have had them by the thousands.

35:48.840 --> 35:50.432
Now, Dr. Bader called you
the day he was killed.

35:50.480 --> 35:52.345
You said so yourself.
Maybe it was the first time

35:52.380 --> 35:54.746
he told you about the mess
he was in. Maybe it wasn't.

35:54.780 --> 35:57.169
Either way, you went down to
the bunker with him that night

35:57.220 --> 35:59.142
to help him steal the pills.

36:00.990 --> 36:03.413
Now, the problem was
the pills didn't exist.

36:03.460 --> 36:06.725
So you did some quick math.

36:06.760 --> 36:07.954
If Bader kept giving
Silver Rail pills,

36:07.990 --> 36:10.197
he was gonna destroy
your practice.

36:10.230 --> 36:11.959
If he stopped
and Silver Rail killed him,

36:12.000 --> 36:14.560
the investigation
into his murder by a drug gang

36:14.600 --> 36:16.238
was going to destroy
your practice.

36:16.270 --> 36:18.261
Either way, he was gonna ruin
your life's work.

36:18.310 --> 36:20.198
HOLMES:
It wasn't fair.

36:20.240 --> 36:22.231
But if he died down there,

36:22.280 --> 36:24.908
the odds would fall
much more in your favor.

36:24.950 --> 36:26.542
You didn't know Ronnie Wright.

36:26.580 --> 36:28.912
You assumed he would not
notify the police

36:28.950 --> 36:31.248
that a murder had happened
inside The Keep

36:31.290 --> 36:34.350
and put his con at risk.
If there was no body found,

36:34.390 --> 36:36.358
that was great.
If the body was found,

36:36.390 --> 36:38.529
it pointed towards Ronnie,
that was still great.

36:38.560 --> 36:41.552
Either way,
your practice remains unscathed.

36:41.600 --> 36:44.398
I don't know where
you're getting any of this.

36:44.430 --> 36:45.966
I told you,

36:46.000 --> 36:48.230
I was with my girlfriend
and her family all weekend

36:48.270 --> 36:49.567
on Lake Ronkonkoma.

36:49.600 --> 36:51.329
We checked,
and that's true.

36:52.810 --> 36:55.335
But there was about
a two-and-a-half-hour window

36:55.380 --> 36:57.234
that night when your girlfriend
and her family

36:57.280 --> 36:58.804
went to a movie without you.

36:58.850 --> 37:00.647
You told them you
weren't feeling well.

37:00.680 --> 37:03.717
That's not enough time to go
to the city and back, but...

37:03.750 --> 37:05.388
the bunker is in Manorville,

37:05.420 --> 37:07.388
which is much closer
to Ronkonkoma.

37:07.420 --> 37:09.980
So if Bader came to you,
you would've had

37:10.020 --> 37:11.681
plenty of time to help him
break into the bunker

37:11.730 --> 37:13.322
to steal the drugs.

37:13.360 --> 37:15.453
GREGSON: That's a photo
of you picking up Bader

37:15.500 --> 37:17.957
at the Ronkonkoma train station.

37:18.000 --> 37:22.790
As far as we know, it's the last
image of Vincent Bader alive.

37:22.840 --> 37:24.398
Now, please,

37:24.440 --> 37:27.603
you want to tell me again
how wrong we are?

37:29.910 --> 37:32.344
Please, come in.

37:42.690 --> 37:44.351
Thank you
for coming.

37:44.390 --> 37:46.483
I know it's contrary
to your wishes.

37:46.530 --> 37:50.057
I broke up with you, so we're
not seeing each other anymore.

37:50.100 --> 37:54.059
But that use of the word
"seeing" is figurative.

37:54.100 --> 37:56.796
We can still see each other.

37:58.810 --> 38:02.075
I-I know that you appreciate
honesty and directness,

38:02.110 --> 38:04.578
so, um,
I'll-I'll be direct with you.

38:04.610 --> 38:06.601
I think you've misjudged me.

38:07.850 --> 38:09.818
I say that without reproach.

38:09.850 --> 38:11.647
I just think you should know.

38:13.020 --> 38:14.351
You said you'd had

38:14.390 --> 38:16.779
two serious relationships
in the past.

38:16.820 --> 38:19.687
It might surprise you to learn
that puts you at least one,

38:19.730 --> 38:21.595
and arguably two, ahead of me.

38:21.630 --> 38:24.793
I had
one great romance

38:24.830 --> 38:26.798
in my life.

38:26.830 --> 38:29.697
One would be hard-pressed
to call her a girlfriend.

38:29.740 --> 38:32.800
And even harder pressed to call
that relationship a success.

38:32.840 --> 38:34.831
I never felt

38:34.880 --> 38:36.609
the need beyond that.

38:36.640 --> 38:38.608
Part of the reason for that

38:38.650 --> 38:41.847
is that relationships
are hard for me.

38:41.880 --> 38:44.383
You sensed
that I was making

38:44.420 --> 38:46.809
an extra effort
to make things work with you.

38:46.850 --> 38:49.410
In that, you were correct.

38:49.460 --> 38:52.827
But you presumed that that was
because you're different.

38:52.860 --> 38:54.828
It is not.

38:54.860 --> 38:57.420
It is because I'm different.

38:58.130 --> 39:00.098
And because

39:00.130 --> 39:02.098
you are the rare woman
I have come across

39:02.140 --> 39:06.600
for whom I believe
that extra effort is worthwhile.

39:06.640 --> 39:08.972
So whatever
the future holds,

39:09.010 --> 39:12.400
whether we see each other again
or not,

39:12.450 --> 39:15.339
I wanted you to know.

39:18.150 --> 39:20.118
Is Joan home?

39:20.150 --> 39:21.754
No.

39:21.790 --> 39:23.781
I requested
she give us some privacy.

39:23.820 --> 39:25.924
Okay.
I think we should have sex now.

39:27.930 --> 39:29.921
Do you want to have sex now?

39:31.030 --> 39:33.999
I-I don't not want to have...

